because css and js may share the same optimization.minizer configuration, if user only want to override css or js minimizer they need to explicitly configure other default minimizer
```js
// override 
module.exports = {
  // ...
  optimization: {
    minimizer: [new rspack.LightningCssMinimizerRspackPlugin()], // this will cause js minizer is overwritten
  },
};
// explicitly override
module.exports = {
  // ...
  optimization: {
    minimizer: [new rspack.LightningCssMinimizerRspackPlugin(), rspack.SwcJsMinimizerRspackPlugin()], // this will cause '...' less useful and user need to custom the default js mimizer
  },
};
```
